In its most remote period, the Latin language was overburdened with long and heavy vowels Some os these archaia long vowels are occasionally found even in later writers, buta great many of them appear still in Plautus and his contemporaries. They are, however, of rare occurrence in Terence, nay, some of them seem to have been entirely lost in the period between Plautus and Terence.
